### 2. Missing Security Headers (OWASP A05)

No HTTP security headers are set. This leaves the app open to clickjacking, MIME-type sniffing, XSS, and protocol downgrade attacks.

```js
// ✅ Fix — add helmet (sets CSP, X-Frame-Options, HSTS, X-Content-Type-Options, etc.)
const helmet = require('helmet');
app.use(helmet());
```

---

### 3. No HTTPS / Transport Encryption (OWASP A02)

The server listens on plain HTTP. All data — including any future auth tokens or credentials — travels unencrypted.

```js
// ✅ Fix — enforce HTTPS (in production, terminate TLS at the load balancer, OR):
const https = require('https');
const fs = require('fs');
const options = {
  key:  fs.readFileSync(process.env.TLS_KEY_PATH),
  cert: fs.readFileSync(process.env.TLS_CERT_PATH),
};
https.createServer(options, app).listen(process.env.PORT || 443);
```

---

### 4. No Rate Limiting (OWASP A04)

The `/users` endpoint can be hammered indefinitely — enabling enumeration, DoS, and data harvesting.

```js
// ✅ Fix — add express-rate-limit
const rateLimit = require('express-rate-limit');
const limiter = rateLimit({
  windowMs: 15 * 60 * 1000, // 15 minutes
  max: 100,
  standardHeaders: true,
  legacyHeaders: false,
});
app.use(limiter);
```

---

### 5. No Input Validation (OWASP A03)

No request body parsing is configured and no validation middleware exists. If the app ever reads `req.body`, `req.query`, or `req.params`, those values go unchecked — opening the door to injection and unexpected behaviour.

```js
// ✅ Fix — parse and validate all inputs explicitly
const express = require('express');
const { body, query, validationResult } = require('express-validator');

app.use(express.json({ limit: '10kb' })); // also prevents large-payload DoS

// Example for a future POST /users endpoint:
app.post('/users',
  body('email').isEmail().normalizeEmail(),
  body('name').isString().trim().isLength({ min: 1, max: 100 }),
  (req, res) => {
    const errors = validationResult(req);
    if (!errors.isEmpty()) return res.status(400).json({ errors: errors.array() });
    // ...
  }
);
```

